# Styling Rules
- Use Tailwind CSS classes, not inline styles
- Follow the existing design system (Shadcn UI)
- Use CSS variables for colors (--primary, --muted, etc.)
- Responsive design: mobile-first approach
- Use semantic HTML elements (nav, main, section, etc.)
- Maintain consistent spacing using Tailwind spacing scale
- Use dark mode compatible colors (use CSS variables)
- Avoid hardcoded colors, use theme variables
- Keep component styles co-located with components when possible
- Use className utilities from @/lib/utils (cn function) for conditional classes
